column5: Hey guys!  Well its that time of year again were the pretty fish come out to play!  After loosing what would have been my first 4 browns yesterday and one this morning i got back out there this afternoon and gave it another go and was rewarded with a beauty!! God dang this are pretty fish it!!!  After releasing the brown i left just in time to beat the intense rainshower   All in all a great day, landed a nice nook and a jack, and saw a nice deer walk right by me while i was fishin!
Nice brown! but please, lets see the salmon too!
I'm right behind you this weekend!!,just have that feeling. Great fish and congrats:thumbsup_anim:
nice fish. whats that cut thing behind his fin?
Looks like a lamprey mark to me.
That's really the only thing it could be.

it was a gross lamprey mark, damn i hate seeing those on fish!  I cant wait for the spring when some more of them come up the creeks and I can kill them  sorry about the mud on the salmon There was nowhere else to land it, the fish was only out of the water for 30 seconds max.
Great brown man, very nice fish
Is that a lighter leash on your waders?  Such a good idea
Nice looking fish! Ive never actually seen one of those in real life!! LOL..
